{"header":"<h1>Module <code><span>Utils</span></code></h1>","type":"documentation","uses_katex":false,"breadcrumbs":[{"name":"Index","href":"../../index.html","kind":"leaf-page"},{"name":"union-find-lattice","href":"../index.html","kind":"page"},{"name":"Utils","href":"#","kind":"module"}],"toc":[],"source_anchor":null,"preamble":"","content":"<div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Functions\"><a href=\"#module-Functions\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Functions/index.html\">Functions</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-HetHashtbl\"><a href=\"#module-HetHashtbl\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"HetHashtbl/index.html\">HetHashtbl</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Most of this code is adapated from the OCaml Standard library's implementation of <code>Hashtbl</code>. It is just adapted for polymorphic types. I.E. a <code>'b t</code> hashtabl binding <code>'a key</code> to <code>('a,'b) value</code> (note that <code>'a</code> is quantified existantially here).</p></div></div><div class=\"odoc-spec\"><div class=\"spec module anchored\" id=\"module-Range\"><a href=\"#module-Range\" class=\"anchor\"></a><code><span><span class=\"keyword\">module</span> <a href=\"Range/index.html\">Range</a></span><span> : <span class=\"keyword\">sig</span> ... <span class=\"keyword\">end</span></span></code></div><div class=\"spec-doc\"><p>Integer ranges (0..n or lo..high), for quick iteration. Inspired by python's <code>range</code> used in for loop, but with a more functional approach.</p></div></div>"}